What's eating you, sweetheart?

03:08.938 --> 03:11.441
Some Jewish family
is claiming that the Nazis

03:11.524 --> 03:13.985
stole my Mondrian from them in the '30s.

03:14.068 --> 03:15.862
They can't take my painting!

03:15.945 --> 03:18.072
- Well, maybe I can help.
- Really?

03:18.156 --> 03:19.490
- I can't pay you.
- Come on.

03:19.574 --> 03:22.327
I got your back with this painting thing.

03:22.410 --> 03:24.787
I actually know a little something
about that world.

03:24.871 --> 03:26.623
Twice a week, I'm a nude model

03:26.706 --> 03:29.751
for what I'm pretty sure is an art class.

03:33.296 --> 03:34.213
Kimmy, wh...

03:34.297 --> 03:38.509
Dong, I know Sonja's at work,
so I knew you'd be alone.

03:38.593 --> 03:41.346
Yes, Sonja is at work.

03:47.352 --> 03:49.604
Look, Sonja found my scrunchie
under your pillow,

03:49.687 --> 03:51.731
so I told her the truth:

03:51.814 --> 03:53.566
that I put it there because I'm trying

03:53.650 --> 03:55.652
to drive the two of you apart.

03:55.735 --> 03:57.904
Oh, how could you?

03:57.987 --> 03:59.948
- What a trick to play.
- I know.

04:00.031 --> 04:01.866
I was being a real slutburger.

04:01.950 --> 04:04.535
But since I'm here...

04:06.829 --> 04:09.374
Mm.

04:09.457 --> 04:11.000
Now it's your turn.

04:11.084 --> 04:12.877
Yeah, take it.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.504
You have to leave!

04:14.587 --> 04:15.672
I'm married!

04:15.755 --> 04:17.423
I cannot suck on your scarf!

04:17.507 --> 04:19.091
Fine, I give up.

04:19.175 --> 04:21.552
Now that I know how you
really feel about me...

04:22.637 --> 04:24.013
goodbye forever.

04:24.097 --> 04:27.016
I hate you so much,

04:27.100 --> 04:28.559
you crazy American witch.

04:29.602 --> 04:30.853
I hate you, too.

04:37.944 --> 04:39.988
Ah, Sonja.

04:40.071 --> 04:41.072
Where did you come from?

04:43.074 --> 04:45.994
This bus is taking forever!

04:48.204 --> 04:50.123
Ermahgerd.

04:50.206 --> 04:52.518
I took the day off for Kimmy,
and now she's out chasing Dong.

04:52.542 --> 04:53.626
You know what?

04:53.710 --> 04:55.086
I'm going out, Mimi Kanassis.

04:55.169 --> 04:56.754
I'm gonna find me an ice cream shop

04:56.838 --> 05:00.258
that won't ask for ID
when I tell them it's my birthday.

05:04.512 --> 05:05.430
Uh-uh, Rick.

05:05.513 --> 05:07.765
I am not coming in to work on my day off.

05:07.849 --> 05:09.600
Titus, we are slammed.

05:09.684 --> 05:11.769
Jason just got a callback for <i>Hamilton,</i>

05:11.853 --> 05:13.479
so we need you to cover his shift.

05:13.563 --> 05:15.481
Why didn't I get an audition for that?

05:15.565 --> 05:17.245
They're just prejudiced 'cause I can't rap

05:17.317 --> 05:18.335
or walk quickly in a circle.

05:18.359 --> 05:20.486
Titus, you know the day
the ground beef expires

05:20.570 --> 05:21.839
is our busiest time of the month.

05:21.863 --> 05:24.741
Just get down here, okay?

05:26.117 --> 05:28.828
When will this liberal war
on Fake Christmas end?

05:28.911 --> 05:30.973
So you're the creep who's trying
to take this painting

05:30.997 --> 05:32.248
out of my children's mouths.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.624
My name is Russ Snyder.

05:33.708 --> 05:36.169
I'm the attorney for the Jewish
Art Reclamation Project,

05:36.252 --> 05:37.253
or JARP!

05:37.336 --> 05:38.671
Please excuse the sling.

05:38.755 --> 05:41.674
I can't discuss it
due to an ongoing lawsuit,

05:41.758 --> 05:44.510
but... the door said "push."

05:44.594 --> 05:45.928
It did, okay?

05:46.012 --> 05:47.055
So every...

05:47.138 --> 05:48.532
All right,
let's get to the matter at hand.

05:48.556 --> 05:50.600
I'm not giving anything to those whiners!

05:50.683 --> 05:52.935
Ms. White, the family
pronounces it "Wiener."

05:53.019 --> 05:55.480
And their claim
to <i>Composition in Burgundy and Gold</i>

05:55.563 --> 05:57.315
is frankly unassailable.

05:57.398 --> 05:59.358
But it's her painting! She bought it!

05:59.442 --> 06:02.779
Yes, only after Hermann Goering stole it

06:02.862 --> 06:04.238
so he could turn it into a dress.

06:04.322 --> 06:06.991
Fortunately, the war ended
before he could create

06:07.075 --> 06:09.243
what would have been
a real statement piece for him.

06:10.244 --> 06:11.913
Now, take these.

06:11.996 --> 06:13.122
Excuse the greasy hands.

06:13.206 --> 06:16.292
I had an <i>empanada con queso</i> in the car.

06:16.375 --> 06:18.628
Now, you can clearly see the evidence here

06:18.711 --> 06:21.631
in this 1936 photo of the family home.

06:21.714 --> 06:25.301
Oh, yeah, they look real Jewish.

06:25.384 --> 06:27.720
What... No, they're standing
in front of the painting.

06:27.804 --> 06:29.180
Really?

06:29.263 --> 06:32.016
Because my painting has colors in it!

06:35.061 --> 06:37.021
- All right, Mr. Dubbin...
- "Mister"?

06:37.105 --> 06:38.106
I like him!

06:38.189 --> 06:40.441
Let me know how your office
would like to proceed.

06:40.525 --> 06:42.443
I'd like to bring some
well-deserved closure

06:42.527 --> 06:45.988
to Harry Wiener and his late wife,
Ivana Eda-Wiener.

06:50.243 --> 06:51.327
What do we do?

06:51.410 --> 06:53.704
Well, we could either
give the painting back,

06:53.788 --> 06:57.083
or I can stall this thing
pretty much forever.

06:57.166 --> 06:58.417
- You can?
- Oh, yeah.

06:58.501 --> 07:00.711
It's the one thing I'm better at
than my brother, David.

07:00.795 --> 07:02.463
You should see him peel an orange.

07:02.547 --> 07:03.714
Perfect!

07:03.798 --> 07:06.968
We just let those bastards
twist in the wind,

07:07.051 --> 07:09.387
like the twins on laundry day.

07:09.470 --> 07:12.557
Exactly, so you just keep me
on retainer indefinitely,

07:12.640 --> 07:14.267
and that painting stays with you.

07:14.350 --> 07:18.688
See, I've got this little
courtroom stalling trick.

07:18.771 --> 07:21.274
It's...

07:21.357 --> 07:22.900
pretty...

07:22.984 --> 07:25.319
amazing.

07:25.403 --> 07:27.405
What...

07:27.488 --> 07:29.157
I...

07:29.240 --> 07:31.701
do...

07:31.784 --> 07:33.828
is...

07:47.425 --> 07:49.886
Well, this is some Fake Christmas.

07:49.969 --> 07:51.387
Where did everybody go, anyway?

07:51.471 --> 07:53.723
Jacqueline took the old lady
to the movies,

07:53.806 --> 07:55.516
and the black guy's dead!

08:03.357 --> 08:04.734
Dong?

08:06.819 --> 08:08.988
How did you fit in Rat Alley?

08:09.071 --> 08:10.990
Why did you take the fall
for me with Sonja?

08:11.073 --> 08:14.202
After the way I treated you,
I was like Cher in <i>Clueless</i>

08:14.285 --> 08:16.287
pretending she wasn't falling for Josh.

08:16.370 --> 08:17.997
As if!

08:18.080 --> 08:20.625
You have every reason to hate me,

08:20.708 --> 08:22.752
but you protected me.

08:22.835 --> 08:24.462
You are such a good person, Kimmy.

08:25.838 --> 08:28.299
Every day, after Sonja
goes to work at the U.N...

08:28.382 --> 08:29.675
Wait, where?

08:29.759 --> 08:30.927
I smell your scrunchie

08:31.010 --> 08:33.221
and dream of when I am
divorced in two years.

08:33.721 --> 08:34.972
As if!

08:35.056 --> 08:36.265
I can't live like this.

08:36.349 --> 08:37.683
- Run away with me!
- What?

08:37.767 --> 08:38.601
No, I...

08:38.683 --> 08:40.102
You were right this whole time.

08:40.186 --> 08:41.812
We shouldn't wait to live our lives.

08:41.895 --> 08:43.096
But you could lose everything.

08:43.147 --> 08:45.358
Without you, I already have.

08:50.613 --> 08:52.990
Sonja knows you work nights,

08:53.074 --> 08:54.992
so take tonight off.

08:55.076 --> 08:56.494
We could go somewhere together.

08:56.577 --> 08:59.288
Like when Joey and Pacey
went to Aunt Gwen's cottage in

08:59.372 --> 09:01.172
"The Creek of the Son of Daw."

09:01.207 --> 09:02.416
But where would we go?

09:02.500 --> 09:04.627
I think we're both
thinking the same thing.

09:04.710 --> 09:06.045
On three.

09:06.128 --> 09:08.005
One, two, three.

09:08.089 --> 09:09.423
Four.

09:09.507 --> 09:10.925
The Poconos.

09:13.928 --> 09:14.845
What are you doing?

09:14.929 --> 09:17.723
You're not Frankenwolf today.
You're filling in for Jason.

09:17.807 --> 09:19.225
The Spooky Gravedigger?

09:19.308 --> 09:20.851
Wait, I'm shift manager?

09:20.935 --> 09:22.270
Do I still get to do my solo?

09:22.353 --> 09:24.897
No, the Invisible Kraken
will take your part.

09:24.981 --> 09:27.525
You have way too much work to do.

09:27.608 --> 09:28.526
Wert?

09:28.609 --> 09:30.570
But those papers
have numbers on them, Rick.

09:30.653 --> 09:31.654
Numbers!

09:31.737 --> 09:34.156
The most boring of all the shapes!

09:40.496 --> 09:41.914
Hey, are you the manager?

09:41.998 --> 09:44.000
I think these Spooky Joes went bad.

09:44.083 --> 09:45.001
Serve them anyway!

09:45.084 --> 09:46.460
Have the customers no toilets?

09:46.544 --> 09:48.796
Have they no trash cans?

09:52.174 --> 09:56.095
Wow, will you look at this place?

09:56.178 --> 09:57.263
Oh, my God.

09:57.346 --> 10:01.559
A Wall Street fella
could really kill a lady in here.

10:03.894 --> 10:05.563
It's all over.

10:06.272 --> 10:08.608
All you got to do is pay the lawyer

10:08.691 --> 10:11.068
to stall for you until the Wieners...

10:15.156 --> 10:17.241
I can't do that!

10:17.325 --> 10:20.077
I... I can't afford to do that.

10:20.161 --> 10:21.996
I'm broke, okay?

10:22.079 --> 10:23.205
Are you kidding?

10:23.289 --> 10:25.541
With this apartment and that wig?

10:25.625 --> 10:26.834
I can't stay here.

10:26.917 --> 10:28.502
That painting was all I had left.

10:29.920 --> 10:33.049
This is the painting?

10:33.132 --> 10:38.054
It's just a bunch of squares
and, like, three paints.

10:38.137 --> 10:40.222
A kid could draw this!

10:40.306 --> 10:42.600
Or we could.

10:46.479 --> 10:50.274
Well, we're getting closer.

10:54.070 --> 10:56.072
Wait, which one is the original?

10:56.155 --> 10:57.657
Oh, God.

10:57.740 --> 10:59.909
I'll have to sell my diamonds and pearls.

10:59.992 --> 11:03.746
Oh, honey, you're gonna have
to sell all your Prince albums.

11:03.829 --> 11:05.956
Well, at least then I can cancel
my insurance policy.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.833
I won't have anything worth insuring.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.418
Hang on.

11:09.502 --> 11:11.962
Is the painting insured?

11:12.046 --> 11:13.172
Well, of course.

11:13.255 --> 11:16.801
A standard policy against fire,
theft, orgy mist, and class war.

11:16.884 --> 11:18.803
Well, why didn't you say so?

11:18.886 --> 11:20.513
That's easy!

11:20.596 --> 11:24.266
All you got to do is say
you're giving the painting back

11:24.350 --> 11:27.937
to Harry Wiener and his daughter,
Anita Wiener-Statt.

11:28.020 --> 11:32.274
But then... Oh, no...
a bunch of dogs eat it!

11:32.358 --> 11:35.736
I know a guy who makes things happen.

11:35.820 --> 11:37.530
What kind of things?

11:37.613 --> 11:41.534
Well, let's just say
the New York Liberty did not beat

11:41.617 --> 11:43.786
the Indiana Fever last night

11:43.869 --> 11:47.331
on the strength of their crisp layups.

11:47.415 --> 11:48.874
Here's the number.

11:50.418 --> 11:51.877
I don't know if I can do that.

11:54.422 --> 11:56.048
Think it over.

12:10.146 --> 12:12.064
I've never stayed at a hotel before,

12:12.148 --> 12:15.609
but I don't think this place is open.

12:15.693 --> 12:18.237
When I called from the road,
the fax line was working.

12:18.320 --> 12:19.905
Nope, it was that raccoon.

12:25.202 --> 12:26.620
Let's find someplace else to stay.

12:26.704 --> 12:28.497
I promised you Aunt Gwen's cottage, and...

12:28.581 --> 12:29.748
This is better.

12:29.832 --> 12:31.542
We can have whatever room we want,

12:31.625 --> 12:34.628
and there's no way
anyone's gonna spot us here.

12:34.712 --> 12:36.964
And look, they must have tennis!

12:37.798 --> 12:40.050
Oh, man, no, I think
this used to be an orange.

12:49.727 --> 12:52.062
I bet this place
used to be really romantic.

12:52.146 --> 12:53.314
Seriously.

12:53.397 --> 12:55.649
I mean, the bathtub's shaped like a butt!

13:02.573 --> 13:04.950
"Warning regarding babies and hot tubs:

13:05.034 --> 13:07.077
Due to the high temperatures
and their ability

13:07.161 --> 13:09.830
to preserve prostatic fluid,
bathe at your own risk

13:09.914 --> 13:11.832
of spontaneous pregnancy."

13:13.334 --> 13:17.213
Wow, that's not where
I thought that was headed.

13:17.296 --> 13:20.674
So we can do whatever we want.

13:22.009 --> 13:24.762
I feel like Kevin McCallister
in <i>Home Alone.</i>

13:24.845 --> 13:26.472
And I'm the old man with the shovel.

13:27.723 --> 13:31.519
Okay, on three, let's both say
what we want to do.

13:31.602 --> 13:34.897
One, two, three.

13:34.980 --> 13:36.666
- Raid the candy machine!
- Lose my American virginity.

13:36.690 --> 13:37.900
Candy machine.

13:46.116 --> 13:47.743
Whoo-hoo!

13:47.826 --> 13:48.744
Oh, yeah!

13:48.827 --> 13:50.996
Whoo!
Whoo!

13:59.129 --> 14:01.048
Please, ma'am,
I'm trying to be reasonable.

14:01.131 --> 14:02.633
Heater's broken on six!

14:02.716 --> 14:04.653
You'll have to take that up
with your credit card company,

14:04.677 --> 14:07.012
but I can offer you
a complimentary waffle.

14:07.096 --> 14:08.013
Mount Breezy Lodge.

14:08.097 --> 14:09.890
Please hold forever.

14:37.918 --> 14:39.378
So what should we do now?

14:39.461 --> 14:41.797
I mean, what else do people
even do in hotels...

14:41.881 --> 14:43.799
with beds...

14:43.883 --> 14:44.884
together?

14:46.093 --> 14:47.177
We don't have to.

14:47.261 --> 14:49.680
No, I want to.

14:50.639 --> 14:53.100
Why do you think I packed
this fancy nightgown?

14:59.523 --> 15:00.858
Let's brush our teeth!

15:06.947 --> 15:08.324
Take a load off.

15:25.507 --> 15:27.259
- Ah!
- Oh, I'm so sorry!

15:27.343 --> 15:28.469
I don't know why I did that!

15:28.552 --> 15:30.304
Did I do something wrong?

15:30.387 --> 15:32.514
No, I just have problems.

15:32.598 --> 15:34.767
I had a weird childhood.

15:34.850 --> 15:37.186
Like Anna Chlumsky in <i>My Girl.</i>

15:39.563 --> 15:41.690
Let's try again. Please.

15:41.774 --> 15:43.692
Okay.

15:43.776 --> 15:44.944
I'm going to kiss you now.

15:45.027 --> 15:46.320
Okay.

15:51.492 --> 15:53.744
Ugh, why does this keep happening?

15:57.998 --> 16:00.918
Damn Creepy Coins.

16:01.001 --> 16:04.129
Why can't we use gift cards
like everybody else?

16:04.213 --> 16:07.591
Hey, Titus, since you're the manager now,

16:07.675 --> 16:09.426
do you mind if I take off a little early?

16:09.510 --> 16:10.427
I do mind.

16:10.511 --> 16:12.113
You're being paid to be here, are you not?

16:12.137 --> 16:14.074
Or perhaps you'd rather
I replace you with a Yuko.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.183
But I have to take Tiny Tim to the doctor.

16:16.266 --> 16:17.601
I don't care about...

16:17.685 --> 16:19.103
Wait a minute, you don't have kids.

16:19.186 --> 16:22.856
Tiny Tim is my nickname for my penis.

